1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Phonemic awareness, which is really about being able to hear the sounds in words.

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Phonics, being able to match those sounds to letters.

3
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Vocabulary, essentially knowing what the words mean.

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Fluency, you develop over time.

5
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Being able to read accurately and quickly.

6
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Your brain can process information very quickly.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
And ultimately, comprehension.

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Making meaning of sentences and extended text.

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:47,000
This is the framework of what a solid reading foundation actually looks like.

10
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
It's not just phonics.

11
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
It is a very comprehensive approach.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:56,000
But phonics and phonemic awareness are the bedrock of that.


